label: Chronometric Age Conversion Protocol (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The method used to convert the chrono:uncalibratedChronometricAge into a chronometric age in years, as captured in chrono:earliestChronometricAge, chrono:earliestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem, chrono:latestChronometricAge, and chrono:latestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem.
dcterms_description: Terms in the chronoiri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Chronometric Age Determined By (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A person, group, or organization that determined the chrono:ChronometricAge.
dcterms_description: Terms in the chronoiri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Chronometric Age Protocol (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A method used to determine the chrono:ChronometricAge.
dcterms_description: Terms in the chronoiri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Chronometric Age Uncertainty Method (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The method used to generate the value of chrono:chronometricAgeUncertaintyInYears.
dcterms_description: Terms in the chronoiri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Earliest Chronometric Age Reference System (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The reference system associated with the chrono:earliestChronometricAge.
dcterms_description: Terms in the chronoiri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Latest Chronometric Age Reference System (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The reference system associated with the chrono:latestChronometricAge.
dcterms_description: Terms in the chronoiri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Material Dated (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The material on which the chrono:chronometricAgeProtocol was actually performed.
